<p>Although some compilers will allow it, the use of <code>sizeof</code> and <code>alignof</code> with arguments that have a <code>void</code> type is
forbidden by both the C and C++ standards.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
void fun() {
  void* p;
  sizeof(*p);  // Noncompliant
  sizeof(void);  // Noncompliant
  alignof(*p);  // Noncompliant
  alignof(void);  // Noncompliant
}
</pre>